#tag("Weyl-eq-plane-wave")
#indent[
  Plane wave solution $Φ e^(- #i p x)$ with $p^2 = m^2$ and $#p Φ = 0$
  
  A linear equation with $det #p = p^2 = 0$ indicates a non-zero solution. The solution space is one-dimensional, and the solution can be written as $Φ = #p^⬨ ξ$ with $dim(im(#p^⬨)) = 1$
  
   
